-- Pakistan Leads England by 55 Runs in Second Cricket Test in Abu Dhabi
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2012-01-27T14:12:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/pakistan-leads-england-by-55-runs-in-second-cricket-test-in-abu-dhabi.html
Pakistan  reached 125-4 in its second
innings in the second cricket test, building a 55-run lead over
England.  Azhar Ali , on 46, and Asad Shafiq, on 35, were unbeaten at
the end of the third day in the five-day match in Abu Dhabi.  Earlier, Stuart Broad hit 58 not out as England took its
first-inning score from 207-5 to  327 all out . Opening batsman
Alastair Cook hit the top score of the innings with 94.  Ali and Shafiq steadied Pakistan with a 71-run partnership
after English spinner Monty Panesar took three wickets to leave
the score at 54-4.  Panesar bowled 25 of the 61 overs, finishing the day 3-44.
Graeme Swann got the other  England  wicket.  Pakistan leads the series 1-0 after a 10-wicket win in the
opening match.  To contact the reporters on this story:
